:"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recvgPc1qs2XrDYQN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recIJFRcqI6KbKgXb","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recX579C9Sml7TQRI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recH30EhVzvnkXBTl","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recvyjBlyKvcsXhY1","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recEP3QZ3HUmIkv4Q","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recA34XfYsCxhyu31","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recKPPAyXwKEJ9Ht8","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec0TFyW8jpdjrmRj","target":"recQ1bj3p4Lj5MYY6","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec0aCLk9wYm27J5Z","ref":"Isa.36.1","text":"Now it came to pass in the fourteenth year of king Hezekiah, that Sennacherib king of Assyria came up against all the defenced cities of Judah, and took them."},{"id":"recK3Fj3RLqRLVs4y","ref":"Isa.36.2","text":"And the king of Assyria sent Rabshakeh from Lachish to Jerusalem unto king Hezekiah with a great army. And he stood by the conduit of the upper pool in the highway of the fuller’s field.","year":-710},{"id":"rec8nPoQLkkqPQJvk","ref":"Isa.36.3","text":"Then came forth unto him Eliakim, Hilkiah’s son, which was over the house, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah, Asaph’s son, the recorder.","year":-710},{"id":"reck5pniwereIoF9l","ref":"Isa.36.4","text":"And Rabshakeh said unto them, Say ye now to Hezekiah, Thus saith the great king, the king of Assyria, What confidence is this wherein thou trustest?","year":-710},{"id":"recCbqVgncHtpq2iI","ref":"Isa.36.5","text":"I say, sayest thou, (but they are but vain words) I have counsel and strength for war: now on whom dost thou trust, that thou rebellest against me?","year":-710},{"id":"recm7kWqJOL49TUsY","ref":"Isa.36.6","text":"Lo, thou trustest in the staff of this broken reed, on Egypt; whereon if a man lean, it will go into his hand, and pierce it: so is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all that trust in him.","year":-710},{"id":"recQi9NOMd5Q1EaMV","ref":"Isa.36.7","text":"But if thou say to me, We trust in the LORD our God: is it not he, whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah hath taken away, and said to Judah and to Jerusalem, Ye shall worship before this altar?","year":-710},{"id":"recD0yo4TaYHEHgEa","ref":"Isa.36.8","text":"Now therefore give pledges, I pray thee, to my master the king of Assyria, and I will give thee two thousand horses, if thou be able on thy part to set riders upon them.","year":-710}]}
